# Replace possible empty values with NaN
df.replace("", np.nan, inplace=True)

# Function to show missing values and their percentages
def missing_data(df):
    l = []
    for col in df.columns:
        missing = df[col].isnull().sum(axis=0)
        percentage = missing/df.shape[0]
        l.append([col,missing,percentage*100])
        df_missing = pd.DataFrame(l, columns = ['Feature','missing','percentage'])
        df_missing = df_missing.sort_values('missing',axis=0, ascending = False)    
    return df_missing

# Check the percentage of missing values
df_missing = missing_data(df)
df_missing = df_missing[df_missing['missing']>0]
df_missing

Recency analysis¶

The cells bellow are transformed in raw nb convert because it takes 7 a 8 hours to run.¶

#Create a list of stores stores = list(set(df1["Point-of-Sale_ID"])) len(stores)#Create a function to save the first sale date and the last sale date of each store datasfirst_stores = [] dataslast_stores = [] for store in stores: dts_st_first = min((df1[(df1["Point-of-Sale_ID"] == store)])['Date']) dts_st_last = max((df1[(df1["Point-of-Sale_ID"] == store)])['Date']) datasfirst_stores.append(dts_st_first) dataslast_stores.append(dts_st_last)#Merge the 2 new columns into a new data frame dfsale_store=pd.DataFrame({ 'Point-of-Sale_ID':stores,'Firstsale_store': datasfirst_stores,'Lastsale_store': dataslast_stores})#Export dataframe to save time dfsale_store.to_csv(os.path.join("dfsale_store.csv"), index=False)#Create a list of products products = list(set(df1["ProductName_ID"])) len(products)#Create a function to save the first sale date and the last sale date of each product datasfirst_prod = [] dataslast_prod= [] for product in products: dts_pr_first = min((df1[(df1["ProductName_ID"] == product)])['Date']) dts_pr_last = max((df1[(df1["ProductName_ID"] == product)])['Date']) datasfirst_prod.append(dts_pr_first) dataslast_prod.append(dts_pr_last)#Merge the 2 new columns into a new data frame dfsale_prod=pd.DataFrame({'ProductName_ID':products,'Firstsale_product': datasfirst_prod,'Lastsale_product': dataslast_prod})#Export dataframe to save time dfsale_prod.to_csv(os.path.join("dfsale_prod.csv"), index=False)
